cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DC 

This paper is about benchmarking the performance of deep learning workloads, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), and distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper specifically focuses on evaluating the time-to-accuracy metric for these workloads, which is a key aspect of machine learning performance. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG, cs.CV, and cs.AI, followed by cs.NE and cs.DC.
